div.p:
What a pity that the Portuguese edition of the Select plants cannot be published;
M had been trying for some time to arrange a Portuguese translation (see M to A. Möller 12 July 1883), including suggesting that it be done in Brazil if not in Portugal (see M to A. Möller, 13 June 1884). A Portuguese translation by Julio Henriques was eventually published, but not until 1905 (B05.13.01). the enlarged North American one has just been published,
B84.13.22. and I am also now preparing a new one for Australia.
